chunk_content: It is likely that at the time of reporting there will be samples that have been collected but for which no result is documented in the register or patient record. This percentage is a proxy measure, relying on PMTCT_STAT_POS + HTS_TST_POS [PostANC1: Pregnancy/L&D] + [PostANC1: BF] modalities as a proxy denominator for total number of HEI. Reviewing infants with a virologic test (N) against this proxy denominator should be done with caution; see assumptions and limitations in the data quality section below. How to collect: This indicator should be collected from the clinical source (i.e., HIV-exposed infant registers or patient records) to ensure unduplicated patient counting. HIV-exposed infant registers should be used to count exposed infants and samples collected for virologic testing. (If available, information could come from electronic systems). If the standard report does not contain all the required information, individual patient files should be used.
